cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of shadow detection and proposes a novel network architecture that uses direction-aware attention mechanism and spatial recurrent neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques and optimization of loss function, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories. The proposed network is evaluated on benchmark datasets, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with image analysis and understanding, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a less likely but still possible category.
